{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Texture animation can also accomplished by setting a texture offset instead of messing directly with UV values.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nfunction spriteAnimate() {\r\n  var st0 = stArray[baseS + 1][baseT];\r\n  sprite.material.map.offset = st0;\r\n  \/\/...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould appreciate a comment from a veteran about updating `faceVertexUvs` after creation. I could not get it to work in your code.","created_at":"2016-12-08T02:25:14.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10312#issuecomment-265635374","id":265635374,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10312","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2NTYzNTM3NA==","updated_at":"2016-12-08T02:46:52.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/265635374","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1297151?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/spirulence","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyOTcxNTE=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"spirulence","type":"User","id":1297151,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spirulence\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"My findings:\r\n\r\nlow-level faceVertexUvs modification still works.\r\n(some people just prefer to do things in this more \"direct\" fashion)\r\nas in:\r\nwater-flow, simply incrementing u coordinate\r\nhttps:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/jmcjc5u\/qz8cbhy4\/\r\n\r\nWhat's not working in r79 (but worked in r70): \r\nif I remove the entire faceVertexUvs and swap in the new ones, as in\r\n  geometry.faceVertexUvs[0] = [];\r\n  geometry.faceVertexUvs[0].push([st0, st1, st2]);\r\n  geometry.faceVertexUvs[0].push([st0, st2, st3]);\r\n\r\nBut if I painstakingly update the values (as in https:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/jmcjc5u\/g7s394ux)\r\nit works OK.\r\n\r\n\tgeometry.faceVertexUvs[0][0][0].x = st0.x;\tgeometry.faceVertexUvs[0][0][0].y = st0.y;\r\n\tgeometry.faceVertexUvs[0][0][1].x = st1.x;\tgeometry.faceVertexUvs[0][0][1].y = st1.y;\r\n\tgeometry.faceVertexUvs[0][0][2].x = st2.x;\tgeometry.faceVertexUvs[0][0][2].y = st2.y;\r\n        \/\/ and so on ....","created_at":"2016-12-08T13:57:14.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10312#issuecomment-265745390","id":265745390,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10312","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2NTc0NTM5MA==","updated_at":"2016-12-08T14:01:14.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/265745390","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/8001352?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/jyunming-chen","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjgwMDEzNTI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"jyunming-chen","type":"User","id":8001352,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jyunming-chen\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> (some people just prefer to do things in this more \"direct\" fashion)\r\n\r\nIt's actually way less efficient, because you need to update the geometry. Even with the simplest of the planes, you (and the gpu) need to update... 2 values (x\/y) * 3 vertices * 2 triangles = 12 values. Instead of just 1 value as @spirulence suggested.","created_at":"2016-12-08T15:58:30.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10312#issuecomment-265776140","id":265776140,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10312","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2NTc3NjE0MA==","updated_at":"2016-12-08T15:58:30.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/265776140","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdo